The **Text** tab allows to configure the text editor by loading an XML file containing the information to be used by Document Composition for managing text content of each document (font styles, color selection, etc.).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## **Inserting an XML file**
- Open the desired XML file using a suitable text editor.

- Copy its text content.

- Paste the text into the editor configuration window. During this operation, Document Composition checks that the syntax of the XML file is correct.

> Note

*The structure of the XML file containing the text configuration is described in detail in DC Text Configuration Settings.*

> Warning

*If you wish to use Dynamic Rich Text elements, additional editor configurations are required. Please refer to the example configurations supplied with the product.*

> Tip

*Follow the Bite Guide on Doxee Application Troubleshooting and Support*

*How to fit a variable text into a fixed space in Document Composition.*
